      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Sure, I'd be happy to help explain quantum entanglement! Quantum entanglement occurs when two or more particles become linked in such a way that the state of one immediately influences the state of another, no matter the distance between them. This is different from classical correlation, where objects can still be connected but don't instantaneously affect each other. In simple terms, entangled particles act as one system, causing correlated changes instantaneously upon measurement.",
