    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The term \"spooky action at a distance\" originated from Albert Einstein famously referring to entanglement as \"spooky\" because the phenomenon seemed puzzling and violated the then accepted principles of local realism. Einstein, Podolsky, and Rosen introduced the EPR paradox to highlight this counterintuitive feature of quantum mechanics. Although entanglement might seem strange when trying to understand it using classical physics concepts, it's a well-established and experimentally verified aspect of quantum physics. So while it might still seem unconventional or \"weird,\" it is very much a part of modern science.",
      "source": "target",
